                <th class="font-display text-base font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-ink py-4 pr-4">Speed Range</th>
                <th class="font-display text-base font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-ink py-4 pr-4">Load</th>
                <th class="font-display text-base font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-ink py-4">Cost</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody class="text-base text-ink-muted">
              <tr class="border-b border-border">
                <td class="py-4 pr-4 font-semibold text-ink">Belt conveyor</td>
                <td class="py-4 pr-4">Primary packaging, pouches, bags</td>
                <td class="py-4 pr-4 font-mono text-sm">20-400 FPM</td>
                <td class="py-4 pr-4 font-mono text-sm">1-100 lbs</td>
                <td class="py-4 font-mono text-sm">$$</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-border">
                <td class="py-4 pr-4 font-semibold text-ink"><a href="/conveyor-types/roller-conveyors/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover">Powered roller</a></td>
                <td class="py-4 pr-4">Cases, cartons, totes</td>
                <td class="py-4 pr-4 font-mono text-sm">30-200 FPM</td>
                <td class="py-4 pr-4 font-mono text-sm">10-500 lbs</td>
                <td class="py-4 font-mono text-sm">$$-$$$</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-border">
                <td class="py-4 pr-4 font-semibold text-ink"><a href="/conveyor-types/mdr-conveyors/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover">MDR</a></td>
                <td class="py-4 pr-4">Case accumulation, zone control</td>
                <td class="py-4 pr-4 font-mono text-sm">30-180 FPM</td>
                <td class="py-4 pr-4 font-mono text-sm">10-250 lbs</td>
                <td class="py-4 font-mono text-sm">$$$</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-border">
                <td class="py-4 pr-4 font-semibold text-ink"><a href="/conveyor-types/transfer-conveyors/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover">Transfer</a></td>
                <td class="py-4 pr-4">Right-angle turns, lane changes</td>
                <td class="py-4 pr-4 font-mono text-sm">30-150 FPM</td>
                <td class="py-4 pr-4 font-mono text-sm">10-4,000 lbs</td>
                <td class="py-4 font-mono text-sm">$$$-$$$$</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-border">
                <td class="py-4 pr-4 font-semibold text-ink"><a href="/conveyor-types/live-roller-conveyors/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover">Live roller</a></td>
                <td class="py-4 pr-4">Continuous case transport</td>
                <td class="py-4 pr-4 font-mono text-sm">30-200 FPM</td>
                <td class="py-4 pr-4 font-mono text-sm">10-300 lbs</td>
                <td class="py-4 font-mono text-sm">$$</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td class="py-4 pr-4 font-semibold text-ink"><a href="/industries/packaging-line-conveyors/pallet/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover">Pallet conveyor</a></td>
                <td class="py-4 pr-4">Palletized loads to stretch wrap/dock</td>
                <td class="py-4 pr-4 font-mono text-sm">20-60 FPM</td>
                <td class="py-4 pr-4 font-mono text-sm">500-4,000 lbs</td>
                <td class="py-4 font-mono text-sm">$$$-$$$$</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Controls and Speed Matching -->
  <section class="py-24 bg-surface" aria-labelledby="controls-heading">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="section-label text-accent mb-4">Controls</div>
      <h2 id="controls-heading" class="font-display text-4xl font-800 text-ink tracking-wide mb-8">
        Speed Matching and Line Control
      </h2>
      <div class="text-lg text-ink-muted leading-relaxed space-y-4">
        <p>
          Every conveyor in a packaging line must match speed with its upstream and downstream machines. Speed mismatches cause product jams, spacing errors, and machine starvation. The packaging line PLC (or individual machine controllers) coordinates conveyor speeds, accumulation zones, and machine start/stop sequences.
        </p>

        <h3 class="font-display text-2xl font-800 text-ink tracking-wide mt-8 mb-4">Variable Frequency Drives (VFDs)</h3>
        <p>
          <a href="/resources/conveyor-motors-drives/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">VFDs</a> control conveyor motor speed by varying the electrical frequency and voltage. They allow precise speed adjustment from the PLC or HMI without mechanical gearbox changes. Most powered conveyors in packaging lines use VFDs for speed control. VFDs also provide soft-start capability, reducing mechanical shock and extending belt and chain life.
        </p>

        <h3 class="font-display text-2xl font-800 text-ink tracking-wide mt-8 mb-4">Photo-Eye Sensors</h3>
        <p>
          Photo-eye sensors detect product presence at accumulation zones, transfer points, and machine infeeds. They trigger conveyor start/stop, zone release in MDR accumulation, and fault signals for jams. Packaging lines use hundreds of photo-eyes. Food-grade lines require stainless steel or sealed photo-eye housings rated to the appropriate IP level.
        </p>

        <h3 class="font-display text-2xl font-800 text-ink tracking-wide mt-8 mb-4">Line Speed Calculation</h3>
        <p>
          The basic speed formula for any conveyor in the line:
        </p>
        <p class="font-mono text-ink bg-surface-dim px-4 py-3 border border-border">
          <strong>Speed (FPM) = Products/min x (Product Length + Gap) / 12</strong>
        </p>
        <p class="mt-4">
          Add 10-15% speed headroom to prevent the conveyor from limiting throughput during peak production. For <a href="/resources/automated-conveyor-systems/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">automated conveyor systems</a> with PLC control, the controller dynamically adjusts speed based on sensor inputs and machine status.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Cost Factors -->
  <section class="py-24 bg-ink-light" aria-labelledby="cost-heading">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="section-label text-accent-bright mb-4">Cost Factors</div>
      <h2 id="cost-heading" class="font-display text-4xl font-800 text-white tracking-wide mb-8">
        Packaging Line Conveyor Cost Drivers
      </h2>
      <div class="text-lg text-white/60 leading-relaxed space-y-4">
        <p>
          Packaging line conveyor costs depend on the number of conveyors, total length, conveyor types, material construction, controls complexity, and installation requirements. The conveyor system typically represents 15-30% of a total packaging line capital budget. <!-- VERIFY: Conveyor system as percentage of total packaging line capital -->
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-3 ml-2 text-white/60">
          <li><strong class="text-white">Total conveyor footage:</strong> More length = more cost, but the relationship is not strictly linear. Longer runs amortize fixed costs (motor, controls) over more footage.</li>
          <li><strong class="text-white">Number of transfers:</strong> Each right-angle transfer, merge, or divert adds a discrete unit cost. Transfers cost disproportionately more per foot than straight runs.</li>
          <li><strong class="text-white">Accumulation requirements:</strong> Zero-pressure MDR accumulation costs 2-3x more per foot than simple powered roller transport.</li>
          <li><strong class="text-white">Material:</strong> <a href="/industries/food-conveyors/" class="text-accent-bright hover:text-white font-semibold">Food-grade stainless</a> costs 2-4x more than painted carbon steel.</li>
          <li><strong class="text-white">Controls integration:</strong> PLC programming, HMI screens, network wiring, and VFDs add 20-40% to hardware cost.</li>
          <li><strong class="text-white">Installation:</strong> Structural supports, electrical connections, and commissioning add 15-30% to equipment cost.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          See our <a href="/resources/conveyor-cost-guide/" class="text-accent-bright hover:text-white font-semibold">conveyor cost guide</a> for detailed pricing factors by conveyor type.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

